@pykong  Sadly, I no longer can edit this PR, since I deleted the old account that made it :disappointed:
Ideally, @vinta could update the URL at merge. :pray:

@vinta There are already 3 PRs (#251, #365, and this one) adding Marshmallow! It is just perfect! Please, add it to the list!

There are also bindings to SQLAlchemy ([marshmallow-sqlalchemy](https://github.com/marshmallow-code/marshmallow-sqlalchemy)), JSONAPI ([marshmallow-jsonapi](https://github.com/marshmallow-code/marshmallow-jsonapi)), and Flask ([flask-marshmallow](https://github.com/marshmallow-code/flask-marshmallow)). There is also [apispec](https://github.com/marshmallow-code/apispec) module for OpenAPI (fka Swagger) Specification integration.

P.S. I'm not sure whether there is a need for a separate section, though; I would put it into Data Validation section. As well as I would move [webargs](https://github.com/sloria/webargs) (a related to marshmallow project from the same author @sloria) to Forms section (from URL Manipulation).

@casperdcl no, use:

`* [tqdm](https://github.com/tqdm/tqdm) - Fast, *extremely simple* extensible progress bar for loops and CLI.`

Simplicity is tqdm's #1 feature.
